HEADWORD: Duebill
<hw>Due"bill`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Com.)</fld> <def>A
brief written acknowledgment of a debt, not made payable to order, like
a promissory note.</def> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

